      "description": "Presenting a pristine 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S, a wide-body masterpiece featuring the 3.6L M96.03 flat-six engine. This unit boasts a documented IMS bearing retrofit and a flawless VarioCam Plus valvetrain system, ensuring peak volumetric efficiency and throttle response. The 6-speed manual gearbox features a precise shift gate with zero synchro hesitation, paired with a resilient Sachs clutch. Its all-wheel-drive system utilizes a viscous-coupling center differential for superior power distribution and longitudinal stability. The chassis remains exceptionally taut, utilizing original M030-spec components for optimal damping and roll stiffness. Cross-drilled rotors and four-piston Monobloc calipers provide firm, fade-free deceleration. This is a turn-key, mechanically superlative example for the serious collector.",
